Collaboration Practices:
•	Daily Stand-Ups: Share progress, challenges, and plans with the team.
•	Sprint Planning Meetings: Coordinate with developers and product managers to define goals.
•	Retrospectives: Discuss what went well and areas for improvement after each sprint.
Communication Tools:
•	Slack: For real-time messaging and quick discussions.
•	JIRA: To track tasks, bugs, and user stories collaboratively.
•	Confluence: Document sharing and collaboration platform.

Ensuring Timely Delivery:
•	Continuous Integration: Regularly integrate and test code to catch issues early.
•	Shared Dashboards: Keep everyone updated on testing progress and bug status.
•	Open Communication: Proactively address potential delays or bottlenecks.
